cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS

This paper deals with computational linguistics and natural language processing, specifically in the area of compositional distributional semantics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves mathematical structures and algorithms, which could place it in cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of vector spaces and algebraic structures suggests a possible fit with cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
